description:
&lt;p&gt;A Band 7 opportunity has arisen at Maidstone &amp; Tunbridge Wells NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The therapy department at Tunbridge Wells hospital is currently seeking a clinical lead Occupational Therapist specialising in orthopaedics, that is highly skilled in working in an acute environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the clinical leadership and operational management of a team of OTs providing input to patients on the trauma and elective orthpaedic wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work alongside collaborative therapy, nursing and medical teams and will require a commitment to multi-disciplinary working, excellent organisation and communications skills and a proactive approach to the development of the service and team members. This is an ideal opportunity for an experienced practitioner wishing to develop advanced clinical and leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your clinical role includes providing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acute cognitive and functional assessments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complex manual handling and equipment provision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complex discharge planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that appointment to this post will be subject to a satisfactory Disclosure &amp; Barring Service Check at &lt;strong&gt;enhanced level. (Enhanced level now includes regulated checks against vulnerable adults and children)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are passionate in supporting our staff to develop and have great opportunities for career progression. We take equality and diversity seriously and seek to empower all diverse groups within our trust. We seek to develop a culture where diversity in all its forms is celebrated. We are committed to ensuring that women are empowered to work at all levels of management and that working patterns are as flexible as possible giving all members of staff opportunity to flourish in using their skills for our patients. We work across our trust to enable those who consider themselves to have a disability both visible and invisible to have access to all they need to thrive in their work environment. We work with Stonewall to embed an inclusive and accepting culture for all lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender staff. We have 78 nationalities working in our trust and we are proud of this. We are active in embracing the ethnic and cultural diversity in our trust. We work to empower people with any protected characteristic to have opportunities to work in an environment that helps them to contribute to the best of their ability, recognising and valuing the unique contributions each of us brings for best quality care and service to our patients. We are committed to supporting the delivery of the Equality Act with zero tolerance for any discrimination, harassment or victimisation of applicants and staff with these protected characteristics&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: &lt;strong&gt;Wednesday 18th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the role or to arrange a visit please contact Jane Duffy Clinical Manager Occupational Therapy on 07523942250&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
